dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bmp1665702615936.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmp1665702615936.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmp1665702615936.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bmp1665702615936\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines how the client area of a primary resizable form is calculated—from the\n    inside or the outside of the upper left corner of the window. In some situations, this can\n    affect whether a horizontal scroll bar is displayed on the bottom of the window.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__section_b35_xm1_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1139600e50\">Syntax</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">FormPositionFromInside</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">On</code> |\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Off</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__section_rqc_zm1_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1139600e70\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__ul_adn_zm1_zvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__li_d51059e1_d51060e1_d51061e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">On</code>—calculate the client area from the upper left corner is on the inside\n          of the sizeable form. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__li_d51062e1_d51063e1_d51064e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Off</code>—calculate the client area from the upper left corner on the outside\n          of the window. This is the default. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__section_ot1_1n1_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1139600e91\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__table_d17945e1_d17946e1_d17947e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Off</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\">Section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzj1665702614359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzj1665702614359.html\" title=\"The [upi] section of the initialization file determines the appearance or behavior of many Universal Presentation Interface (UPI) objects under Microsoft Windows.\">[upi]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bmp1665702615936__section_nmv_bn1_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1139600e133\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">By default, a resizable primary form, with the horizontal position set to 1 is displayed\n        without a horizontal scrollbar. Prior to 9.6.02, such a scrollbar was displayed on Windows\n        Vista and Windows 7.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Use this switch only if you want to have the old behavior.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526127\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526127\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "FormPositionFromInside Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 27, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determines how the client area of a primary resizable form is calculated—from the inside or the outside of the upper left corner of the window. In some situations, this can affect whether a horizontal scroll bar is displayed on the bottom of the window. Syntax FormPositionFromInside { = } On | Off Arguments On —calculate the client area from the upper left corner is on the inside of the sizeable form. Off —calculate the client area from the upper left corner on the outside of the window. This is the default. Defaults Default value Off Section [upi] Description By default, a resizable primary form, with the horizontal position set to 1 is displayed without a horizontal scrollbar. Prior to 9.6.02, such a scrollbar was displayed on Windows Vista and Windows 7. Use this switch only if you want to have the old behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}